http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 12 Oct 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2016; 29(41) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=21197


Hemorrhagic septicemia, Kazakhstan
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 12 Oct 2016 from Dr Samat Tyulegenov, director general, RSE "National Reference Center for Veterinary", Ministry of Agriculture, Astana, Kazakhstan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 14 Sep 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 23 Sep 2016
Reason for notification: first occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Pasteurella multocida_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Zhaskairat village, Oiyl, Kyzylkogy, Gur Yev [Atyrau]
Date of start of the outbreak: 14 Sep 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2141 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Camelidae / 101 / 0 / 0 / 0
Equidae / 504 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep/goats / 16588 / 571 / 388 /0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0 / 0 / - / 0
Camelidae / 0 / 0 / - / 0
Equidae / 0 / 0 / - / 0 /
Sheep/goats / 3.44 / 2.34 / 67.95 / 2.34
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the local executive authority of Oiyl took the decision to apply quarantine from 3 Oct 2016.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection/disinfestations; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; control of wildlife reservoirs; zoning; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Reference Center for Veterinary Sciences (national laboratory) / Sheep/goats / bacteriological examination / 11 Oct 2016 / Positive
National Reference Center for Veterinary Sciences (national laboratory) / Sheep/goats / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 11 Oct 2016 / Positive
Republican Veterinary laboratory (regional laboratory) / Sheep/goats / bacteriological examination / 23 Sep 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

