communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Kazakhstan previously reported hemorrhagic septicemia in June 2015 and again in May 2016, in other zones of the country.

The event in June 2015 involved 4 outbreaks affecting Saiga antelope (_Saiga tatarica_). See report event summary and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=17785.

The event in May 2016 involved in cattle. See event summary and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=20143

Both events have been communicated as resolved.

See map of Kazakhstan at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/kazakhstan-political-map.htm. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4556387,46186.]
